<item>
            <title>[LU-14786] lod creates broken debugfs symlinks</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14786</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The lod layer creates a broken symlink from &lt;tt&gt;/sys/kernel/debug/lustre/lov/lustre-MDT0000-mdtlov&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;../lod/lustre-MDT0000-mdtlov&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;# ls -l /sys/kernel/debug/lustre/lov/lustre-MDT0000-mdtlov
lrwxrwxrwx 1 root root 0 Jun 24 07:55 /sys/kernel/debug/lustre/lov/lustre-MDT0003-mdtlov -&amp;gt; ../lod/lustre-MDT0000-mdtlov
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would be good to have a test for broken symlinks in procfs, sysfs, debugfs. &lt;tt&gt;find PATH... -xtype l&lt;/tt&gt; can be used to print broken symlinks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
